The paper deals with the problem of maximizing the mean-payoff value with high probability while satisfying a parity objective in a Markov decision process (MDP) with unknown probabilistic transition function and unknown reward function. This involves learning and optimization, which are key topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) as it deals with optimizing a payoff function. Additionally, the paper involves discrete mathematics (cs.DM) as it deals with formalizing and proving results related to MDPs. Finally, the paper involves control systems (cs.SY) as it deals with decision making in a stochastic environment.
